## Environment variables

- App-specific vars are prefixed `{{constantCase name}}_` and typed in `agent/lib/env.ts`.
  Add new ones there and to `.env.example`; caching picks them up via the
  `{{constantCase name}}_*` wildcard in `turbo.json`.
- `AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY` is required for live model calls only. Deterministic
  evals (`eval:ci`) and unit tests run with zero env vars.

## Run and verify just this app

```bash
pnpm --filter {{name}} run dev        # local TUI / REPL
pnpm --filter {{name}} run lint       # biome
pnpm --filter {{name}} run typecheck
pnpm --filter {{name}} run build      # eve build
pnpm --filter {{name}} run test       # vitest (tests/)
pnpm --filter {{name}} run eval:ci    # deterministic evals, tag "ci", mock model
pnpm --filter {{name}} run eval       # all evals, live model
```

## Rules

- Dependency versions come from the pnpm catalog (`"catalog:"`) — never write
  a version number in `package.json`.
- Never import from a sibling app under `apps/*`.
- Keep deterministic evals key-free: anything tagged `ci` must pass with no
  env vars set.
